-- 2012-02-24T08:14:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-24/boyner-rises-in-istanbul-after-report-owner-is-buying-ykm-chain.html
Boyner Buyuk Magazicilik AS (BOYNR) , a
Turkish department store chain, headed for the highest level
since October after a report its owner has bought a majority
stake in the YKM chain of department stores.  Boyner Holding AS bought 63 percent of YKM, which operates
57 department stores in Turkey, Haberturk newspaper reported
today, without saying where it got the information.  The shares were suspended from trading on request of the
company, which didnâ€™t announce any transaction. Boyner gained
1.3 percent to 3.06 liras, giving the company a market value of
281.7 million lira ($160 million), before trade was suspended.  Boyner Holding AS bought 63 percent of YKM, which operates
